---
import MinimalDarkLayout from "@/layouts/MinimalDarkLayout.astro";

const experiments = [
  {
    title: "Experiment 2",
    href: "https://github.com/ara-foundation/forum",
    subtitle: "Minimal community-first forum, no blockchain.",
  },
  {
    title: "Experiment 3",
    href: "https://github.com/ara-foundation/app-v1",
  },
  {
    title: "Experiment 4",
    href: "https://github.com/ara-foundation/ara-v1",
  },
  {
    title: "Experiment 5",
    href: "https://github.com/ara-foundation/ara-v2",
  },
  {
    title: "Experiment 6",
    href: "https://github.com/ara-foundation/ara-v3",
  },
  {
    title: "Experiment 7",
    href: "https://github.com/ara-foundation/app/tree/pre-blockchain",
    subtitle:
      "Social media for sustainable open source projects with semantic payment distribution.",
  },
] as const;
---

<MinimalDarkLayout title="Ara Roadmap">
  <div class="roadmap-main">
    <div class="roadmap-shell">
      <aside class="roadmap-nav-wrap">
        <nav class="roadmap-nav" aria-label="Roadmap section navigation">
          <p class="roadmap-nav-label">Roadmap</p>
          <a href="#pre-2024-2026" class="nav-link nav-link-pre"
            >Pre with date (2024-2026)</a
          >
          <a href="#now" class="nav-link nav-link-now">Now</a>
          <a href="#from-2026" class="nav-link nav-link-next">2026-onward</a>
          <a href="#join-us" class="nav-link nav-link-join">Join us</a>
        </nav>
      </aside>

      <div class="roadmap-content">
        <section id="pre-2024-2026" class="roadmap-section section-pre">
          <p class="s-label">Pre with date (2024-2026)</p>
          <h1 class="section-title">What Has Been Done</h1>

          <div class="timeline">
            <article class="timeline-item">
              <p>
                First it was a 3D software environment with AI assistant. The
                idea was right but asbtract. 3D space was a desktop app. It
                didn't work out because the UI metaphor was not properly built,
                and the blockchain side was not ready.
              </p>
              <div class="shot-grid three">
                <figure class="screenshot-photo">
                  <img
                    src="/roadmap/roadmap-3d-1.png"
                    alt="3D environment screenshot showing AI assistant and command panel."
                    loading="lazy"
                  />
                  <figcaption>screenshot 1 - 3D environment</figcaption>
                </figure>
                <figure class="screenshot-photo">
                  <img
                    src="/roadmap/roadmap-3d-2.png"
                    alt="3D environment screenshot showing UI panel and browser action."
                    loading="lazy"
                  />
                  <figcaption>screenshot 2 - 3D environment</figcaption>
                </figure>
                <figure class="screenshot-photo">
                  <img
                    src="/roadmap/roadmap-3d-3.png"
                    alt="3D environment screenshot showing multiple users and Ara transfers."
                    loading="lazy"
                  />
                  <figcaption>screenshot 3 - 3D environment</figcaption>
                </figure>
              </div>
              <p>
                Demo showcase available on
                <a
                  href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=suOaUQmMSGo&t=41s"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener">YouTube</a
                >.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="timeline-item">
              <p>
                Then it moved to the web to ship faster. It experiment with 2D
                new metaphor for malleable interface: instead typography based
                component, its like a universe with galaxies (projects) and
                stars (users).
              </p>
              <figure class="screenshot-photo">
                <img
                  src="/roadmap/roadmap-galaxy-interface.png"
                  alt="Galaxy interface screenshot from Ara web version."
                  loading="lazy"
                />
                <figcaption>screenshot - galaxy interface</figcaption>
              </figure>
              <p>
                The site itself came with meta tools that let you step outside
                the page.
              </p>
              <figure class="screenshot-photo">
                <img
                  src="/roadmap/roadmap-meta-tools-scrolled.png"
                  alt="Scrolled Ara page showing meta tools and galaxy background."
                  loading="lazy"
                />
                <figcaption>
                  screenshot - scrolled version with meta tools visible
                </figcaption>
              </figure>
              <p>
                UI is malleable with AI: in screenshot below you can see how to
                customize zoom controller with AI.
              </p>
              <figure class="screenshot-photo">
                <img
                  src="/roadmap/roadmap-zoom-controller.png"
                  alt="Ara interface screenshot with zoom controller customization panel."
                  loading="lazy"
                />
                <figcaption>screenshot - zoom controller</figcaption>
              </figure>
            </article>

            <article class="timeline-item">
              <p>
                It didn't work out because I was trying to push it as a social
                network. Then I tried to work on each of the Ara component and
                as only focus on malleable interface was misdirecting
                trajectory.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="timeline-item">
              <p>
                After countless feedbacks I finally get the proper idea and
                structure and here we are.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>

          <div class="completion-block">
            <h2 class="sub-title">Completed</h2>
            <ul class="done-list">
              <li>
                <a href="/ara.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
                  ><strong>Whitepaper</strong></a
                >
                - the full framework, published April 2026.
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href="https://hyperpayment.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
                  ><strong>Hyperpayment protocol</strong></a
                >
                - pays money according to semantics, not manual invoicing or
                fixed subscriptions.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Malleable interface that people need</strong> (draft).
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="now" class="roadmap-section section-now">
          <p class="s-label">Now</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">What Is Now</h2>
          <article class="phase-card">
            <div class="phase-head">
              <h3 class="phase-title">Phase I - Cascade Fund</h3>
              <span class="phase-state state-active">Active</span>
            </div>
            <p>
              The first version brings together two communities: users who want
              to feel like kings of their computers, and the open source
              developers who build the tools they depend on.
            </p>
            <p>
              Users pay open source projects monthly. In return they choose from
              three options:
            </p>
            <ul class="detail-list">
              <li>Prevent features or API deprecation.</li>
              <li>Add features to the API that make their lives easier.</li>
              <li>Turn the project into Ara.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Turning into Ara has two forms.</p>
            <ol class="detail-list ordered">
              <li>
                Split the interface, data, and logic so personal data stays on
                the local side.
              </li>
              <li>
                Bring open source communities together to create shared
                protocols and messages, so apps are aligned with each other.
              </li>
            </ol>
            <p>
              What users get: a bundle of open source software where features
              and APIs are guaranteed not to disappear, all data stays local,
              and nothing is locked to a vendor.
            </p>
            <p>
              To surface what matters, Ara will build an analyzer that reads
              what APIs exist and how users actually use them - then suggests
              improvements that save time.
            </p>
            <p class="onboard-line">
              <span>Onboards:</span> open source developers and their users
            </p>
          </article>
        </section>

        <section id="from-2026" class="roadmap-section section-next">
          <p class="s-label">2026-onward</p>

          <article class="phase-card">
            <div class="phase-head">
              <h3 class="phase-title">Phase II - Project Management</h3>
              <span class="phase-state state-next">Coming next</span>
            </div>
            <p>
              Built on what Cascade Fund proved, the second phase is a project
              management environment that runs in the browser.
            </p>
            <p>
              Local first: all your data stays on your machine. AI ready: the
              model runs locally, trained on what you already own. Composable:
              apps are Lego bricks built on other apps, reshuffled without
              worrying about licenses.
            </p>
            <p>
              This is the malleable surface. Software you own, not software you
              rent.
            </p>
            <p class="onboard-line">
              <span>Onboards:</span> designers, power users, productivity-focused
              teams
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="phase-card">
            <div class="phase-head">
              <h3 class="phase-title">Phase III - Blockchain</h3>
              <span class="phase-state state-horizon">The horizon</span>
            </div>
            <p>
              The third phase puts the foundation on-chain. Two wings: one that
              stores the semantics of open source software, one that runs
              recommendation on top of those semantics.
            </p>
            <p>
              The blockchain here is not a financial instrument - it is
              collective wisdom. A trustless recommendation engine that surfaces
              what users actually need, not what someone paid to promote.
            </p>
            <p>
              And if it succeeds: it whitewashes blockchain from its infamous
              reputation.
            </p>
            <p class="onboard-line">
              <span>Onboards:</span> node operators, the broader ecosystem
            </p>
          </article>
        </section>

        <section id="join-us" class="roadmap-section section-join">
          <p class="s-label">Join us</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">Stay updated and collaborate</h2>
          <p>
            Lastly, to keep updated follow on our social media. Or if you want
            to collaborate mail me at
            <a href="mailto:medet@ara.foundation">medet@ara.foundation</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <aside class="roadmap-right-wrap">
        <section class="roadmap-right-panel" aria-label="Experiments source code">
          <p class="roadmap-right-label">Code archive</p>
          <h2 class="roadmap-right-title">Experiment GitHub links</h2>
          <ol class="experiment-list">
            {
              experiments.map((exp, i) => (
                <li class="experiment-item">
                  <span class="experiment-index">{i + 2}.</span>
                  <div>
                    <a href={exp.href} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                      {exp.title}
                    </a>
                    {"subtitle" in exp && exp.subtitle ? (
                      <p>{exp.subtitle}</p>
                    ) : null}
                  </div>
                </li>
              ))
            }
          </ol>
        </section>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</MinimalDarkLayout>

<style>
  @import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=DM+Mono:wght@300;400&family=Source+Serif+4:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..60,300;0,8..60,400;1,8..60,300&display=swap");

  .roadmap-main {
    --bg: #0d0d0d;
    --line: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    --line2: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.16);
    --text: #e8e2d8;
    --dim: #aba293;
    --pre-accent: #d4824a;
    --now-accent: #5abf9f;
    --next-accent: #8f81ff;
    --join-accent: #e0b85a;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: "Source Serif 4", Georgia, serif;
  }

  .roadmap-main * {
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  .roadmap-main a {
    color: inherit;
  }

  .roadmap-shell {
    max-width: 1450px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 2rem 6rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 2rem;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(200px, 250px) minmax(0, 1.45fr) minmax(220px, 280px);
  }

  .roadmap-nav-wrap {
    position: relative;
  }

  .roadmap-nav {
    position: sticky;
    top: 2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: #121212;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }

  .roadmap-nav-label {
    font-family: "DM Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.64rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.26em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    color: var(--dim);
  }

  .nav-link {
    text-decoration: none;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding: 0.65rem 0.75rem;
    font-family: "DM Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    transition:
      border-color 0.2s,
      background-color 0.2s,
      color 0.2s;
  }

  .nav-link:hover {
    border-color: var(--line2);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
  }

  .nav-link-pre {
    color: var(--pre-accent);
  }

  .nav-link-now {
    color: var(--now-accent);
  }

  .nav-link-next {
    color: var(--next-accent);
  }

  .nav-link-join {
    color: var(--join-accent);
  }

  .roadmap-content {
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: #111;
  }

  .roadmap-right-wrap {
    position: relative;
  }

  .roadmap-right-panel {
    position: sticky;
    top: 2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: #121212;
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .roadmap-right-label {
    font-family: "DM Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.64rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.26em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
    color: var(--dim);
  }

  .roadmap-right-title {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-family: "Playfair Display", serif;
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .experiment-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .experiment-item {
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    padding: 0.7rem 0.75rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .experiment-index {
    font-family: "DM Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--dim);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .experiment-item a {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    font-family: "Playfair Display", serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .experiment-item p {
    margin: 0.35rem 0 0;
    font-family: "DM Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--dim);
  }

  .roadmap-section {
    padding: 3.4rem 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .roadmap-section:last-child {
    border-bottom: 0;
  }

  .section-pre {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #15110e 0%, #111 100%);
  }

  .section-now {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0f1715 0%, #101212 100%);
  }

  .section-next {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #131224 0%, #111 100%);
  }

  .section-join {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #1a1710 0%, #111 100%);
  }

  .s-label {
    margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    font-family: "DM Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.28em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .s-label::before,
  .s-label::after {
    content: "";
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--line2);
    max-width: 52px;
  }

  .section-title {
    margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
    font-family: "Playfair Display", serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4.5vw, 2.6rem);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .sub-title {
    margin: 0 0 0.7rem;
    font-family: "Playfair Display", serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  .timeline {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.2rem;
  }

  .timeline-item,
  .phase-card,
  .completion-block {
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25);
    padding: 1.25rem 1.2rem;
  }

  .timeline-item p,
  .phase-card p,
  .section-join p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.75;
    font-size: 1.04rem;
  }

  .timeline-item p:last-child,
  .phase-card p:last-child,
  .section-join p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .shot-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.8rem;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .shot-grid.two {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .screenshot-placeholder {
    min-height: 140px;
    border: 1px dashed var(--line2);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1rem;
    font-family: "DM Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--dim);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .screenshot-photo {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--line2);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .screenshot-photo img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    min-height: 140px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .screenshot-photo figcaption {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    font-family: "DM Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--dim);
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18);
  }

  .done-list,
  .detail-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.55rem;
  }

  .done-list li,
  .detail-list li {
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .phase-card + .phase-card {
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
  }

  .phase-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .phase-title {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: "Playfair Display", serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .phase-state {
    font-family: "DM Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    border: 1px solid currentColor;
    padding: 0.36rem 0.58rem;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .state-active {
    color: var(--now-accent);
  }

  .state-next {
    color: #8ab0ff;
  }

  .state-horizon {
    color: #c09bff;
  }

  .onboard-line {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    color: var(--dim);
  }

  .onboard-line span {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .section-pre .s-label,
  .section-pre a {
    color: var(--pre-accent);
  }

  .section-now .s-label,
  .section-now a {
    color: var(--now-accent);
  }

  .section-next .s-label,
  .section-next a {
    color: var(--next-accent);
  }

  .section-join .s-label,
  .section-join a {
    color: var(--join-accent);
  }

  .section-pre .section-title,
  .section-now .section-title,
  .section-next .section-title,
  .section-join .section-title {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .section-pre .timeline-item p,
  .section-now .phase-card p,
  .section-next .phase-card p,
  .section-join p {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  @media (max-width: 1000px) {
    .roadmap-shell {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      padding: 2rem 1rem 4rem;
    }

    .roadmap-nav {
      position: static;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .roadmap-nav-label {
      grid-column: 1 / -1;
    }

    .roadmap-section {
      padding: 2.2rem 1.25rem;
    }

    .roadmap-right-panel {
      position: static;
    }

    .phase-head {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .roadmap-nav {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .shot-grid.two {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
